dq=f\left(x\right)\cdot dr
\frac{dq}{dt}=f\left(x\right)\cdot \frac{dr}{dt}
\Delta t \to 0
dq
\frac{dq}{dt}dt
dr
\frac{dr}{dt}dt
\frac{dq}{dt} = f(x)\frac{dr}{dt}
\frac{dq}{dt}dt = f(x)\frac{dr}{dt}dt
f
x,y,z,t
 df = \frac{\partial f}{\partial t} dt + \frac{\partial f}{\partial x} dx+\frac{\partial f}{\partial y} dy +\frac{\partial f}{\partial z} dz
x, y ,z
t
 dx = \frac{\partial x}{\partial t} dt \,; dy = \frac{\partial y}{\partial t} dt ; dz = \frac{\partial z}{\partial t} dt
 df = \left(\frac{\partial f}{\partial t}  + \frac{\partial f}{\partial x} \frac{\partial x}{\partial t}  + \frac{\partial f}{\partial y}  \frac{\partial y}{\partial t} + \frac{\partial f}{\partial z} \frac{\partial z}{\partial t} \right)dt
